snippet: Now that Nevada has finally finished counting ballots, there are three interesting data-driven takeaways from the state.
abstract: Now that Nevada has finally finished counting ballots, there are three interesting data-driven takeaways from the state.
lead_paragraph: Nevada Republicans have finally finished counting caucus ballots, and Mitt Romney was declared the winner there with just slightly more than 50 percent of the vote. Newt Gingrich finished second with 21 percent, followed closely by Ron Paul at 19 percent. Rick Santorum was fourth with 10 percent of the vote.
